cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new algorithm that improves the performance of imitation learning through the use of probabilistic methods. It also involves the use of neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as the paper discusses the use of imitation learning in robotics and the challenges that come with it. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms to improve the performance of imitation learning. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the impact of safety on the performance of imitation learning in robotics. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly involve computer vision, but it does use neural networks which are commonly used in computer vision applications.
